Restored full text of the inscription:

1.[Wahabum bin Ḍaʾisum, the serv]ant of Yadaʿʾīl Bayyin bi[n Sumhūyafaʿ and ʾĪlī-]
2.[samaʿ Dhubyān bin Malkī]karib, the two kings of Ḥaḍramōt, [has directed and constructed the wall]
3.[of Mayfaʿat out of stone and woo]d and brick. And may the [magistrate who acts in his capacity as the magistrate of May-]
4.[faʿat be aided by Siyān and Ḥawl and] Ḥalayʾīl and the king of Ḥaḍramō[t against that of which he is negligent and]
5.[repair the walls of Mayfaʿa]t and their towers. And may he re[pair the damage of that which has been strengthened]
6.[and that which has not been stre]ngthened. And may he continue to ser[ve the king of Ḥaḍramōt. And may he]
7.[repair that portion] of the walls and the towers [which has suffered damage.]</tei:ab>
